title: Australia faces climbing ‘economic challenges’ under Labor
description: The Nightly Chief Writer Aaron Patrick joins Sky News Australia to analyse the climbing national debt in Australia as interest rates suffer under the rise of inflation.  “The servicing costs are just getting higher and higher,” Mr Patrick said.  “This has got to be one of the biggest economic challenges facing the country.”

title: ‘Terribly sad’: AGL Energy abandons Gippsland offshore wind project plans
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says that AGL Energy has abandoned plans for its offshore wind project in Gippsland.  “AGL Energy has abandoned its offshore wind project in Victoria’s Gippsland region,” Mr Bond said.  “The Allan government had hoped that Gippsland could become a hub for large-scale renewable energy investment, but the company has determined that the project would fold.”

title: ‘Extraordinary’: Former artistic director calls for funding freeze of Creative Australia
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says Creative Australia’s funding is now in the spotlight after former artistic director of Opera Australia Lyndon Terracini called for a funding freeze.   “One of the country's most experienced and respected cultural leaders has called for a funding freeze and an urgent review into Creative Australia,” Mr Bond said.  “Lyndon Terracini is the former artistic director of Opera Australia, and he slammed Creative Australia’s method of handing out money by peer review.”

title: Renewable energy projects blasted amid wind project abandonments
description: Sky News senior reporter Caroline Marcus scrutinises renewable energy projects.  This comes amid AGL Energy’s abandonment of its Gippsland offshore wind project.  “It only works when the wind blows and when the sun shines,” Ms Marcus said.

title: AGL Gippsland wind project would not have been profitable until 23rd century
description: Wordsmith and broadcaster Kel Richards mocks AGL’s abandonment of Gippsland’s offshore wind project.  “My guess is, that the subsidies look so good,” Mr Richards said.  “This thing will turn a profit about when the Starship Enterprise is launched in the 23rd century.”

title: ‘Just Google everything’: New term ‘stupidogenic’ defines society turning into ‘idiots’
description: Writer and broadcaster Kel Richards presents a new term “stupidogenic” where a society is full of “stuff” to make you stupid.  “People once knew how to look things up in reference books,” Mr Richards said.  “Now, we just Google everything.”

title: ‘Noise is part of apartment living’: Complaints over communal areas raised
description: Sky News senior reporter Caroline Marcus highlights how people who choose apartment living “cannot accept” it is a communal living space.  “We have a dog, he has lived there for longer than most people in that apartment,” Ms Marcus said.  “Suddenly … complains about it, they are working from home, and I get it … if you want no noise you will have to move out to the suburbs.”

title: ‘We are victims of it’: Society’s over-reliance on technology discussed
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says he has become “so used” to relying on technology over learnt knowledge.  Mr Hildebrand said relying on technology to get somewhere even if he already knew the way was concerning.  Over-reliance on technology in such ways has been labelled the ‘death of thinking’.

title: Almost a million Australians work multiple jobs under Labor’s cost of living pressure
description: Sky News host Paul Murray highlights how almost a million Australians are working more than one job to make ends meet.

title: ‘A world of trouble’: Major bushfires burn across NSW
description: On tonight’s episode of Paul Murray Live, Sky News host Paul Murray discusses the major bushfires in NSW, cost of living, US politics and more.

title: ‘Not enough houses’: Aussies believe immigration too high under Labor
description: Sky News host Paul Murray analyses the “overall picture” of Australian politics as the issue of immigration confronts many Aussies during the cost of living crisis.

title: ‘Pining for his daughter’: Thomas Markle would ‘love to meet his grandkids’
description: TalkTV Host Mark Dolan comments on the recent drama concerning the Markle family.  “It looks like there’s misinformation coming from Montecito, which is not out of character,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “It’s very sad … he’s pining for his daughter, he’d love to meet his grandkids.”

title: Keir Starmer labelled ‘out of his depth’ amid possible Unite Union-Labour split
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan claims the Unite Union is the UK Labour Party's primary supporter and is now contemplating withdrawing support due to UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer's “incompetence”.    “It’s the leader of the Unite Union who is one of the biggest funders of the governing Labour Party,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Labour relies on them every year to keep campaigning and keep running as an organisation … the unions were the basis of the Labour Party as we know it, and now they want out, they consider Starmer to be out of his depth, incompetent.”

title: ‘She cancels people’: Concerns over Meghan’s actions around estranged father
description: TalkTV Host Mark Dolan analyses Thomas Markle’s plea to his estranged daughter for his grandchildren.  “Meghan has got history on this, she cancels people, her ex-husband … the minute she got that role in ‘Suits’, he was gone,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Her best friend … over a non-existent race row … this woman is very dangerous.”

title: Anika Wells under fire over taxpayer-funded expense claims
description: Communications Minister Anika Wells is under fire over thousands of dollars in expenses billed to the taxpayer.  The Opposition has claimed the minister should repay some of the money.   This issue comes ahead of the Australia's under 16 social media ban, which will be overseen by Ms Wells.
